  "prompt": "What is fiscal capacity distance?",
  "response": "Fiscal capacity distance refers to the disparity in the ability of different regions or jurisdictions to generate revenue through taxation and other fiscal means. It is a measure of the inequality in the financial resources available to governments at different levels, which can impact their ability to provide services and infrastructure to their populations. Fiscal capacity distance is often considered in discussions about fiscal federalism and the allocation of resources between central and subnational governments to ensure equitable access to public goods and services.",
